@startuml e2e-08-kb-learn-repl
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
title E2E-08: kb learn — REPL Loop (Follow-up + Suggestions)

actor User
participant "CLI\nmain.py" as CLI
participant "LearnSession\nlearn.py" as LEARN
participant "Retriever\nretriever.py" as RET
participant "VectorStore\n(ChromaDB)" as VS
participant "EmbedFn\n(embedder.py)" as EMB
participant "PTC\nptc.py" as PTC
participant "ptc_scripts/\nsummarize_chunk.py" as SCRIPT
participant "LocalAdapter\nor PremiumAdapter" as MODEL

note over CLI : Enters REPL after initial explanation\n(see E2E-07). last_chunks and last_query\nare retained between turns.

== REPL Turn: User selects numbered suggestion ==

User -> CLI : "2"
CLI -> CLI : resolve input "2" → suggestions[1]\n= "What is SSDT Shadow and how does it differ?"
CLI --> User : → What is SSDT Shadow and how does it differ?

CLI -> LEARN : follow_up("What is SSDT Shadow and how does it differ?")
LEARN -> LEARN : anchored = "SSDT: What is SSDT Shadow\n  and how does it differ?"
LEARN -> RET : search(anchored, top_k=5)
RET -> EMB : encode(anchored)
EMB --> RET : query_vector[N]
RET -> VS : query(query_vector, n_results=20)
VS --> RET : [{chunk, score, heading, file}, ...]
RET --> LEARN : [Chunk(...), ...]

alt no chunks returned
  LEARN --> CLI : ("", [])
  CLI --> User : "No KB content found for that question.\n  Try a different phrasing."
  CLI --> User : [re-display previous suggestions]
  note right : REPL loop continues\nwith last_chunks / last_query unchanged
end

LEARN -> PTC : compress(chunks, "summarize_chunk")
PTC -> SCRIPT : run(chunk_dicts)
note right : Extracts first 2 sentences per section\n— no model call
SCRIPT --> PTC : "[SSDT Shadow] The SSDT Shadow is a copy of\nthe SSDT used exclusively for Win32k.sys...\n[Kernel Callbacks] ..."
PTC --> LEARN : PTCResult(compressed_text, raw_tokens, compressed_tokens)

LEARN -> MODEL : generate(answer_prompt +\n  ptc_result.compressed_text)
MODEL --> LEARN : "The SSDT Shadow is a separate dispatch table\nused by Win32k.sys for GUI subsystem calls.\nUnlike the main SSDT it is not protected by..."
LEARN --> CLI : (answer_text, new_chunks)

CLI --> User : <answer text>\n(local)\n\n────────────────────────\nSources:\n  • windows-internals.md › SSDT Shadow

== New Suggestions for this turn ==

CLI -> LEARN : suggest(new_chunks, last_query="What is SSDT Shadow...")
LEARN -> MODEL : generate(suggest_prompt +\n  new chunk headings + last_query)
note right : Always uses local adapter.\nNever raises — returns [] on failure (PM4).
MODEL --> LEARN : '["How does PatchGuard protect\n SSDT Shadow?", "What is KeServiceDescriptorTable?",\n "How do AV products hook SSDT Shadow?"]'
LEARN --> CLI : ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3"]

CLI --> User : ────────────────────────\nSuggested follow-ups:\n  [1] How does PatchGuard protect SSDT Shadow?\n  [2] What is KeServiceDescriptorTable?\n  [3] How do AV products hook SSDT Shadow?\n\nAsk a follow-up (1-3, your own question, 'quiz', or 'quit'):

== REPL Turn: User types 'quiz' ==

User -> CLI : "quiz"
CLI --> User : Quiz yourself: python cli/main.py quiz --topic 'SSDT'\n\nSession ended. Tokens used (approx): 420

== REPL Turn: User types 'quit' or Ctrl+C ==

User -> CLI : "quit"  [or Ctrl+C]
CLI --> User : Session ended. Tokens used (approx): 420
note right : KeyboardInterrupt caught cleanly (PM3).\nNo stack trace.

@enduml
